    "content": "<h1 id=\"getting-started\">Getting Started<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#getting-started\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites\">Prerequisites<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#prerequisites\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Requirement</th>\n<th>Minimum</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Go</td>\n<td>1.24</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Canon EOS camera</td>\n<td>WiFi / PTP/IP enabled</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Storage backend</td>\n<td>SMB share, FTP server, S3 bucket, Azure Blob, or GCS bucket</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 id=\"1-enable-wifi-on-the-camera\">1. Enable WiFi on the camera<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#1-enable-wifi-on-the-camera\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<p>On a Canon EOS 2000D (and most modern EOS bodies):</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Menu → WiFi/Bluetooth → WiFi function → Other cameras / Connect</strong>  </li>\n<li>Note the <strong>SSID</strong> and connect your machine to that network, or join the same LAN if using infrastructure mode.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The camera listens on <strong>TCP port 15740</strong> (PTP/IP).</p>\n<h2 id=\"2-install-from-source\">2. Install from source<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#2-install-from-source\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<div class=\"language-bash highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span id=\"__span-0-1\"><a id=\"__codelineno-0-1\" name=\"__codelineno-0-1\" href=\"#__codelineno-0-1\"></a>git<span class=\"w\"> </span>clone<span class=\"w\"> </span>https://github.com/pacorreia/canon-proxy.git\n</span><span id=\"__span-0-2\"><a id=\"__codelineno-0-2\" name=\"__codelineno-0-2\" href=\"#__codelineno-0-2\"></a><span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>canon-proxy\n</span><span id=\"__span-0-3\"><a id=\"__codelineno-0-3\" name=\"__codelineno-0-3\" href=\"#__codelineno-0-3\"></a>go<span class=\"w\"> </span>build<span class=\"w\"> </span>-o<span class=\"w\"> </span>canon-proxy<span class=\"w\"> </span>./cmd/canon-proxy\n</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"3-configure\">3. Configure<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#3-configure\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<div class=\"language-bash highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span id=\"__span-1-1\"><a id=\"__codelineno-1-1\" name=\"__codelineno-1-1\" href=\"#__codelineno-1-1\"></a>cp<span class=\"w\"> </span>config.example.yaml<span class=\"w\"> </span>config.yaml\n</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Edit <code>config.yaml</code> — at minimum set <code>camera.host</code> to your camera's IP:</p>\n<div class=\"language-yaml highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span id=\"__span-2-1\"><a id=\"__codelineno-2-1\" name=\"__codelineno-2-1\" href=\"#__codelineno-2-1\"></a><span class=\"nt\">camera</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n</span><span id=\"__span-2-2\"><a id=\"__codelineno-2-2\" name=\"__codelineno-2-2\" href=\"#__codelineno-2-2\"></a><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"nt\">host</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">&quot;192.168.2.70&quot;</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"c1\"># your camera&#39;s IP</span>\n</span><span id=\"__span-2-3\"><a id=\"__codelineno-2-3\" name=\"__codelineno-2-3\" href=\"#__codelineno-2-3\"></a><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"nt\">port</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"l l-Scalar l-Scalar-Plain\">15740</span>\n</span><span id=\"__span-2-4\"><a id=\"__codelineno-2-4\" name=\"__codelineno-2-4\" href=\"#__codelineno-2-4\"></a><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"nt\">poll_interval</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"l l-Scalar l-Scalar-Plain\">5s</span>\n</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"admonition tip\">\n<p class=\"admonition-title\">Settings are stored in the database</p>\n<p>After the first run, all settings are persisted in the SQLite database and editable live from the <strong>Settings</strong> page in the web UI. Changes to <code>config.yaml</code> are ignored once a setting exists in the DB.</p>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"4-run\">4. Run<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#4-run\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<div class=\"language-bash highlight\"><pre><span></span><code><span id=\"__span-3-1\"><a id=\"__codelineno-3-1\" name=\"__codelineno-3-1\" href=\"#__codelineno-3-1\"></a>./canon-proxy<span class=\"w\"> </span>--config<span class=\"w\"> </span>config.yaml\n</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Open <strong><a href=\"http://localhost:9090\">http://localhost:9090</a></strong> — you should see the web UI with thumbnails appearing as the initial sync runs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"5-configure-a-storage-backend\">5. Configure a storage backend<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#5-configure-a-storage-backend\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<p>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> in the web UI and configure your preferred backend. For example, to use an SMB share:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Field</th>\n<th>Value</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Backend</td>\n<td><code>smb</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Host</td>\n<td><code>192.168.2.9</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Share</td>\n<td><code>photos</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Username</td>\n<td><code>user</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Password</td>\n<td><code>secret</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Path</td>\n<td><code>/uploads</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 id=\"6-queue-images-for-upload\">6. Queue images for upload<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#6-queue-images-for-upload\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<p>Images are discovered automatically and shown in the web UI. Select the ones you want and click <strong>Queue selected</strong> or <strong>Queue all</strong> to start uploading.</p>\n<p>Uploads start as soon as an image is queued.</p>\n<h2 id=\"next-steps\">Next Steps<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#next-steps\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../configuration/\">Configuration reference</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"../architecture/\">Architecture overview</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"../deployment/\">Docker &amp; Kubernetes deployment</a></li>\n</ul>",
